tafsir[2]{c,v,t}:
  40,52,"Man gets a glimpse of this possibility at the onset of old age. When a man grows very old, all his powers are taken away from him, so much so that he becomes as weak and helpless as he was as a small child. But, man is so foolish that he does not learn a lesson from this."
  40,54,"The Quran’s veracity will be evident only to those whose souls are truly alive, and only such people will admit the Truth."